g; 6 — propodeum; 7 — petiole; 8 — ovipositor sheath." captionText-4="Fig. 10. Trioxys curvicaudus, ♀ (1–5) and Trioxys pallidus, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — antenna; 2, 7 — forewing; 3, 8 — propodeum; 4, 9 — petiole; 5 a, 5 b, 10 — ovipositor sheath and prongs. Рис. 10. Trioxys curvicaudus, ♀ (1–5) и Trioxys pallidus, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — усик; 2, 7 — переднее крыло; 3, 8 — проподеум; 4, 9 — стебелёк; 5 a, 5 b, 10 — створки яйцеклада и пронги." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467466" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449137" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449139" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449143" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467470" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6467466/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6449137/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6449139/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6449143/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/6467470/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF84FF9FF305FB93EC7CFBAF" box="[531,588,1081,1108]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">6–10</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
), differing by: 1) antenna less thickened at apex, with preapical and apical flagellomeres not fused; 2) flagellomere 1 (F1) with londitudinal placodes; 3) wider fore wings: 2.7 times as long as wide; 4) propodeum without carinae; 5) more slender petiole; 6) brown abdomen and antenna; 7) less thin and sharp ovipositor sheath; 8) host range.
</paragraph>
